CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION multiply(num1 string num2 string) RETURNS string  
        IF num1 EQUALS string zero OR num2 EQUALS string zero  
            RETURN string zero  
        END IF  

        SET result TO a list of zeros with the LENGTH OF num1 PLUS the LENGTH OF num2  

        SET num1 TO the reversal of num1  
        SET num2 TO the reversal of num2  

        FOR i FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF num1 MINUS one  
            FOR j FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF num2 MINUS one  
                SET mul TO the character code of the element at position i of num1 MINUS the character code of string zero MULTIPLIED BY the character code of the element at position j of num2 MINUS the character code of string zero  
                SET p1 TO i PLUS j  
                SET p2 TO i PLUS j PLUS one  
                SET sum TO mul PLUS the element at position p1 of result  

                SET the element at position p1 of result TO sum MODULO ten  
                INCREMENT the element at position p2 of result BY the integer division of sum BY ten  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  

        SET result_str TO the concatenation of the string representations of the elements of result in reverse order  
        RETURN result_str with all leading string zeros removed  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION canJump(nums)  
        SET farthest TO zero  
        FOR i FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF nums MINUS one  
            IF i GREATER THAN farthest  
                RETURN false  
            END IF  
            SET possible_reach TO i PLUS element at position i of nums  
            IF possible_reach GREATER THAN farthest  
                SET farthest TO possible_reach  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        IF farthest GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO the LENGTH OF nums MINUS one  
            RETURN true  
        ELSE  
            RETURN false  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION combine WITH PARAMETERS n k  
        FUNCTION backtrack WITH PARAMETERS start path  
            IF the LENGTH OF path EQUALS k  
                APPEND a COPY OF path TO result  
                RETURN  
            END IF  
            FOR i FROM start TO n PLUS one  
                APPEND i TO path  
                CALL backtrack WITH ARGUMENTS i PLUS one path  
                REMOVE the LAST ELEMENT FROM path  
            END FOR  
        END FUNCTION  
        SET result TO an EMPTY LIST  
        CALL backtrack WITH ARGUMENTS one AN EMPTY LIST  
        RETURN result  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION minCut(s)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s  
        IF n LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO one  
            RETURN zero  
        END IF  
        
        SET is_palindrome TO a two dimensional collection of size n by n filled with FALSE  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            SET element at position i at position i of is_palindrome TO TRUE  
        END FOR  
        
        FOR length FROM two TO n  
            FOR start FROM zero TO n MINUS length  
                SET end TO start PLUS length MINUS one  
                IF length EQUALS two  
                    SET element at position start at position end of is_palindrome TO the condition that element at position start of s EQUALS element at position end of s  
                ELSE  
                    SET element at position start at position end of is_palindrome TO the condition that element at position start of s EQUALS element at position end of s AND the element at position start PLUS one at position end MINUS one of is_palindrome  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        SET min_cuts TO a collection of size n filled with zero  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            IF element at position zero at position i of is_palindrome  
                SET element at position i of min_cuts TO zero  
            ELSE  
                SET element at position i of min_cuts TO positive infinity  
                FOR j FROM one TO i  
                    IF element at position j at position i of is_palindrome AND element at position j MINUS one of min_cuts PLUS one LESS THAN element at position i of min_cuts  
                        SET element at position i of min_cuts TO element at position j MINUS one of min_cuts PLUS one  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN element at position n MINUS one of min_cuts  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION countPrimes WITH PARAMETER n  
        IF n LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO two  
            RETURN zero  
        END IF  
        SET is_prime TO an empty list  
        FOR index FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            APPEND True TO is_prime  
        END FOR  
        SET element at position zero of is_prime TO False  
        SET element at position one of is_prime TO False  
        SET limit TO the integer part of the square root of n  
        FOR start FROM two TO limit PLUS one  
            IF element at position start of is_prime EQUALS True  
                SET multiple TO start MULTIPLIED BY start  
                WHILE multiple LESS THAN n  
                    SET element at position multiple of is_prime TO False  
                    INCREMENT multiple BY start  
                END WHILE  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        SET count TO zero  
        FOR each value IN is_prime  
            IF value EQUALS True  
                INCREMENT count BY one  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN count  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION numSquares(n)  
        SET dp TO a list of size n PLUS one FILLED WITH infinite value  
        SET the element at position zero of dp TO zero  
        SET squares TO an empty list  
        SET i TO one  
        WHILE i MULTIPLIED BY i IS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO n  
            APPEND i MULTIPLIED BY i TO squares  
            INCREMENT i BY one  
        END WHILE  
        FOR i FROM one TO n  
            FOR each square IN squares  
                IF i IS LESS THAN square  
                    BREAK the inner loop  
                END IF  
                SET dp at position i TO the smaller value BETWEEN dp at position i AND dp at position i MINUS square PLUS one  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN the element at position n of dp  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maxProduct(words)  
        SET word_sets TO empty list  
        FOR each word IN words  
            APPEND the set of characters of word TO word_sets  
        END FOR  
        
        SET max_product TO zero  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF words MINUS one  
            FOR j FROM i PLUS one TO the LENGTH OF words MINUS one  
                IF the intersection of element at position i of word_sets AND element at position j of word_sets EQUALS empty set  
                    SET product TO the LENGTH OF element at position i of words MULTIPLIED BY the LENGTH OF element at position j of words  
                    IF product GREATER THAN max_product  
                        SET max_product TO product  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN max_product  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION coinChange(coins, amount)  
        SET dp TO a list of amount PLUS one elements each set TO amount PLUS one  
        SET element at position zero of dp TO zero  
        FOR each a FROM one TO amount  
            FOR each coin IN coins  
                IF a MINUS coin IS GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero  
                    SET dp at position a TO the minimum BETWEEN dp at position a AND dp at position a MINUS coin PLUS one  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        IF dp at position amount IS NOT EQUAL TO amount PLUS one  
            RETURN dp at position amount  
        ELSE  
            RETURN minus one  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION isSelfCrossing(distance)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF distance  
        IF n LESS THAN four  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        FOR i FROM three TO n MINUS one  
            IF element at position i of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS two of distance AND element at position i MINUS one of distance LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS three of distance  
                RETURN True  
            END IF  
            IF i GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO four AND element at position i MINUS one of distance EQUALS element at position i MINUS three of distance AND element at position i PLUS element at position i MINUS four of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS two of distance  
                RETURN True  
            END IF  
            IF i GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO five AND element at position i MINUS two of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS four of distance AND element at position i MINUS three of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS one of distance AND element at position i MINUS one of distance PLUS element at position i MINUS five of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS three of distance AND element at position i PLUS element at position i MINUS four of distance GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i MINUS two of distance  
                RETURN True  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN False  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION countNumbersWithUniqueDigits(n)  
        IF n EQUALS zero THEN  
            RETURN one  
        END IF  
        IF n EQUALS one THEN  
            RETURN ten  
        END IF  
        SET count TO ten  
        SET available_digits TO nine  
        SET choices TO nine  
        FOR i FROM two TO n INCLUSIVE  
            SET choices TO choices MULTIPLIED BY available_digits  
            SET count TO count PLUS choices  
            SET available_digits TO available_digits MINUS one  
        END FOR  
        RETURN count  
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION isRectangleCover(rectangles)  
        SET X1 TO positive infinity  
        SET Y1 TO positive infinity  
        SET X2 TO negative infinity  
        SET Y2 TO negative infinity  
        
        SET points TO empty set  
        SET area TO zero  
        
        FOR each rectangle WITH elements x1 y1 x2 y2 IN rectangles  
            IF X1 GREATER THAN x1 THEN  
                SET X1 TO x1  
            END IF  
            IF Y1 GREATER THAN y1 THEN  
                SET Y1 TO y1  
            END IF  
            IF X2 LESS THAN x2 THEN  
                SET X2 TO x2  
            END IF  
            IF Y2 LESS THAN y2 THEN  
                SET Y2 TO y2  
            END IF  
            
            SET current_area TO (x2 MINUS x1) MULTIPLIED BY (y2 MINUS y1)  
            INCREMENT area BY current_area  
            
            FOR each point p IN list containing element pair of x1 and y1 element pair of x1 and y2 element pair of x2 and y1 element pair of x2 and y2  
                IF points CONTAINS p THEN  
                    REMOVE p FROM points  
                ELSE  
                    ADD p TO points  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        SET expected_area TO (X2 MINUS X1) MULTIPLIED BY (Y2 MINUS Y1)  
        IF area NOT EQUALS expected_area THEN  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        
        SET expected_points TO set containing element pair of X1 and Y1 element pair of X1 and Y2 element pair of X2 and Y1 element pair of X2 and Y2  
        IF points NOT EQUALS expected_points THEN  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        
        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION wordsTyping(sentence, rows, cols)  
        SET s TO the concatenation of all elements of sentence with a single space between each followed by a single space character  
        SET total_length TO the LENGTH OF s  
        SET position TO zero  
        
        FOR each iteration IN the range from one TO rows  
            INCREMENT position BY cols  
            
            IF the element at position MODULO total_length of s EQUALS a space character  
                INCREMENT position BY one  
            ELSE  
                WHILE position GREATER THAN zero AND the element at position MINUS one MODULO total_length of s NOT EQUALS a space character  
                    DECREMENT position BY one  
                END WHILE  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN position DIVIDED BY total_length  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION originalDigits(s)  
        SET count TO the collection of character frequencies in s  
        SET digits TO a list of ten zeros representing counts for zero to nine  
        SET element at position zero of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter z in count  
        SET element at position two of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter w in count  
        SET element at position four of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter u in count  
        SET element at position six of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter x in count  
        SET element at position eight of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter g in count  
        SET element at position three of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter h in count MINUS element at position eight of digits  
        SET element at position five of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter f in count MINUS element at position four of digits  
        SET element at position seven of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter s in count MINUS element at position six of digits  
        SET element at position nine of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter i in count MINUS element at position five of digits MINUS element at position six of digits MINUS element at position eight of digits  
        SET element at position one of digits TO the number of occurrences of character corresponding to letter o in count MINUS element at position zero of digits MINUS element at position two of digits MINUS element at position four of digits  
        SET result TO an empty list  
        FOR each index FROM zero TO nine  
            FOR each repetition FROM one TO element at position index of digits  
                APPEND string representation of index TO result  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        SET final_string TO the concatenation of all elements in result  
        RETURN final_string  
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION findMaxForm(strs, m, n)  
        SET dp TO a two dimensional list with the dimensions of m plus one by n plus one where each element is zero  
        FOR each string s IN strs  
            SET count_0 TO the number of elements EQUALS to zero in the string s  
            SET count_1 TO the number of elements EQUALS to one in the string s  
            FOR variable i FROM m DOWN TO count_0  
                FOR variable j FROM n DOWN TO count_1  
                    SET dp at position i and position j TO the maximum value between dp at position i and position j AND the value of dp at position i MINUS count_0 and position j MINUS count_1 PLUS one  
                END FOR  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN dp at position m and position n  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION kInversePairs(n, k)  
        SET MOD TO one billion PLUS seven  
        SET dp TO a two dimensional list of zeros with dimension n PLUS one by k PLUS one  
        SET element at position zero of element at position zero of dp TO one  
        
        FOR i FROM one TO n  
            SET prefix_sum TO zero  
            FOR j FROM zero TO k  
                SET prefix_sum TO prefix_sum PLUS element at position j of element at position i MINUS one of dp  
                IF prefix_sum GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO MOD  
                    SET prefix_sum TO prefix_sum MINUS MOD  
                END IF  
                IF j GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO i  
                    SET prefix_sum TO prefix_sum MINUS element at position j MINUS i of element at position i MINUS one of dp PLUS MOD  
                    IF prefix_sum GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO MOD  
                        SET prefix_sum TO prefix_sum MINUS MOD  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
                SET element at position j of element at position i of dp TO prefix_sum  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN element at position k of element at position n of dp  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION scheduleCourse(courses)  
        SORT courses BY the second element of each course representing the last day of the course  
        SET max_heap TO an empty list  
        SET current_end_day TO zero  
        FOR each course IN courses  
            SET duration TO the first element of course representing the duration of the course  
            SET last_day TO the second element of course representing the last day of the course  
            IF current_end_day PLUS duration LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO last_day THEN  
                ADD the negative value of duration TO max_heap using a heap push operation  
                INCREMENT current_end_day BY duration  
            ELSE IF max_heap IS NOT empty AND the negation of the first element of max_heap GREATER THAN duration THEN  
                INCREMENT current_end_day BY duration PLUS the heap pop operation result from max_heap  
                ADD the negative value of duration TO max_heap using a heap push operation  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN the length of max_heap  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION judgeSquareSum WITH parameter c  
        SET left TO zero  
        SET right TO integer VALUE OF the SQUARE ROOT OF c  
        WHILE left LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO right holds  
            SET current_sum TO left MULTIPLIED BY left PLUS right MULTIPLIED BY right  
            IF current_sum EQUALS c THEN  
                RETURN true  
            ELSE IF current_sum LESS THAN c THEN  
                INCREMENT left BY one  
            ELSE  
                DECREMENT right BY one  
            END IF  
        END WHILE  
        RETURN false  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION predictPartyVictory(senate)  
        ASSIGN reference TO new double-ended queue named radiant  
        ASSIGN reference TO new double-ended queue named dire  

        FOR each index i AND character s IN senate  
            IF character s EQUALS the character representing Radiant party  
                APPEND index i TO radiant  
            ELSE  
                APPEND index i TO dire  
            END IF  
        END FOR  

        WHILE radiant is not empty AND dire is not empty  
            REMOVE and ASSIGN the first element from radiant TO r_index  
            REMOVE and ASSIGN the first element from dire TO d_index  

            IF r_index LESS THAN d_index  
                APPEND r_index PLUS the length of senate TO radiant  
            ELSE  
                APPEND d_index PLUS the length of senate TO dire  
            END IF  
        END WHILE  

        IF radiant is not empty  
            RETURN the word Radiant  
        ELSE  
            RETURN the word Dire  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION minimumDeleteSum(s1, s2)  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF s1  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s2  
        
        CREATE a two dimensional list dp WITH dimensions m PLUS one BY n PLUS one INITIALIZED WITH zeroes  
        
        FOR j FROM one TO n  
            SET element at position j of the first row of dp TO element at position j MINUS one of the first row of dp PLUS ASCII value of character at position j MINUS one of s2  
        END FOR  
        
        FOR i FROM one TO m  
            SET element at position i of the first column of dp TO element at position i MINUS one of the first column of dp PLUS ASCII value of character at position i MINUS one of s1  
        END FOR  
        
        FOR i FROM one TO m  
            FOR j FROM one TO n  
                IF character at position i MINUS one of s1 EQUALS character at position j MINUS one of s2  
                    SET element at position i , position j of dp TO element at position i MINUS one , position j MINUS one of dp  
                ELSE  
                    SET element at position i , position j of dp TO the MINIMUM OF element at position i MINUS one , position j of dp PLUS ASCII value of character at position i MINUS one of s1 AND element at position i , position j MINUS one of dp PLUS ASCII value of character at position j MINUS one of s2  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN element at position m , position n of dp  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION longestWord(words)  
        SORT words BY the LENGTH OF element AND THEN BY element IN LEXICOGRAPHICAL ORDER  
        SET valid_words TO an empty set  
        SET longest_word TO an empty string  
        FOR each word IN words  
            IF the LENGTH OF word EQUALS one OR the substring of word from position one TO position LENGTH OF word MINUS one IS IN valid_words  
                ADD word TO valid_words  
                IF the LENGTH OF word GREATER THAN the LENGTH OF longest_word  
                    SET longest_word TO word  
                END IF  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN longest_word  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION pourWater(heights WITH TYPE List of integers volume WITH TYPE integer k WITH TYPE integer) RETURNS List of integers  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF heights  
        
        FOR each iteration FROM one TO volume  
            SET i TO k  
            WHILE i GREATER THAN zero AND element at position i MINUS one of heights LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i of heights  
                DECREMENT i BY one  
            END WHILE  
            WHILE i LESS THAN k AND element at position i of heights EQUALS element at position i PLUS one of heights  
                INCREMENT i BY one  
            END WHILE  
            IF i LESS THAN k  
                INCREMENT element at position i of heights BY one  
                CONTINUE  
            END IF  
            
            SET i TO k  
            WHILE i LESS THAN n MINUS one AND element at position i PLUS one of heights LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO element at position i of heights  
                INCREMENT i BY one  
            END WHILE  
            WHILE i GREATER THAN k AND element at position i of heights EQUALS element at position i MINUS one of heights  
                DECREMENT i BY one  
            END WHILE  
            IF i GREATER THAN k  
                INCREMENT element at position i of heights BY one  
                CONTINUE  
            END IF  
            
            INCREMENT element at position k of heights BY one  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN heights  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION canTransform(start parameter, end parameter)  
        SET start_filtered TO empty list  
        FOR index FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF start parameter MINUS one  
            SET character_at_index TO element at position index of start parameter  
            IF character_at_index NOT EQUALS the character X  
                APPEND tuple of character_at_index AND index TO start_filtered  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        SET end_filtered TO empty list  
        FOR index FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF end parameter MINUS one  
            SET character_at_index TO element at position index of end parameter  
            IF character_at_index NOT EQUALS the character X  
                APPEND tuple of character_at_index AND index TO end_filtered  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        IF the LENGTH OF start_filtered NOT EQUALS the LENGTH OF end_filtered  
            RETURN false  
        END IF  
        FOR each pair of tuples first_pair AND second_pair IN the PAIRWISE ITERATION OF start_filtered AND end_filtered  
            SET character_one TO the first element of first_pair  
            SET index_one TO the second element of first_pair  
            SET character_two TO the first element of second_pair  
            SET index_two TO the second element of second_pair  
            IF character_one NOT EQUALS character_two  
                RETURN false  
            END IF  
            IF character_one EQUALS the character L AND index_one LESS THAN index_two  
                RETURN false  
            END IF  
            IF character_one EQUALS the character R AND index_one GREATER THAN index_two  
                RETURN false  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN true  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION validTicTacToe(board)  
        SET countX TO zero  
        FOR each row IN board  
            INCREMENT countX BY the number of occurrences of character X in row  
        END FOR  
        SET countO TO zero  
        FOR each row IN board  
            INCREMENT countO BY the number of occurrences of character O in row  
        END FOR  

        IF countX LESS THAN countO OR countX GREATER THAN countO PLUS one  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  

        FUNCTION check_win(player)  
            FOR each row IN board  
                IF row EQUALS player repeated three times in succession  
                    RETURN True  
                END IF  
            END FOR  

            FOR col FROM zero TO two  
                IF element at position col of first row EQUALS player AND element at position col of second row EQUALS player AND element at position col of third row EQUALS player  
                    RETURN True  
                END IF  
            END FOR  

            IF element at position zero of first row EQUALS player AND element at position one of second row EQUALS player AND element at position two of third row EQUALS player  
                RETURN True  
            END IF  
            IF element at position two of first row EQUALS player AND element at position one of second row EQUALS player AND element at position zero of third row EQUALS player  
                RETURN True  
            END IF  
            RETURN False  
        END FUNCTION  

        SET winX TO result of invoking check_win with parameter character X  
        SET winO TO result of invoking check_win with parameter character O  

        IF winX AND winO  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        IF winX AND countX EQUALS countO  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        IF winO AND countX NOT EQUALS countO  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  

        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION soupServings(n)  
        IF n GREATER THAN four thousand eight hundred THEN  
            RETURN one point zero  
        END IF  
        SET n TO n PLUS twenty four DIVIDED BY twenty five  
        SET memo TO empty dictionary  
        FUNCTION dp(a, b)  
            IF tuple of a AND b EXISTS IN memo THEN  
                RETURN value of tuple of a AND b IN memo  
            END IF  
            IF a LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND b LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO zero THEN  
                RETURN zero point five  
            END IF  
            IF a LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO zero THEN  
                RETURN one point zero  
            END IF  
            IF b LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO zero THEN  
                RETURN zero point zero  
            END IF  
            SET prob TO zero point two five MULTIPLIED BY sum of dp of a MINUS four AND b PLUS dp of a MINUS three AND b MINUS one PLUS dp of a MINUS two AND b MINUS two PLUS dp of a MINUS one AND b MINUS three  
            SET value of tuple of a AND b IN memo TO prob  
            RETURN prob  
        END FUNCTION  
        RETURN dp of n AND n  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION flipgame(fronts, backs)  
        SET same TO empty set  
        FOR each pair of front_card AND back_card IN fronts AND backs simultaneously  
            IF front_card EQUALS back_card  
                ADD front_card TO same  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        SET all_numbers TO empty set  
        FOR each number IN fronts  
            ADD number TO all_numbers  
        END FOR  
        FOR each number IN backs  
            ADD number TO all_numbers  
        END FOR  
        SET good_numbers TO empty set  
        FOR each number IN all_numbers  
            IF number NOT IN same  
                ADD number TO good_numbers  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        IF the LENGTH OF good_numbers IS GREATER THAN zero  
            SET minimum_good_number TO the smallest element IN good_numbers  
            RETURN minimum_good_number  
        ELSE  
            RETURN zero  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION numFactoredBinaryTrees(arr)  
        SET MOD TO ten raised to the power of nine PLUS seven  
        SORT arr IN ascending order  
        SET dp TO an empty mapping FROM elements of arr TO the number one FOR each element in arr  
        FOR index i FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF arr MINUS one  
            SET num TO element at position i of arr  
            FOR index j FROM zero TO i MINUS one  
                SET potential_factor TO element at position j of arr  
                IF num MODULO potential_factor EQUALS zero THEN  
                    SET right_child TO num DIVIDED BY potential_factor  
                    IF right_child EXISTS AS a key IN dp THEN  
                        SET dp of num TO dp of num PLUS dp of potential_factor MULTIPLIED BY dp of right_child  
                        SET dp of num TO dp of num MODULO MOD  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        SET total TO zero  
        FOR each value IN dp values  
            INCREMENT total BY value  
        END FOR  
        RETURN total MODULO MOD  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION shortestPathLength(graph)  
        IF graph EQUALS empty collection THEN  
            RETURN zero  
        END IF  
      
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF graph  
        SET queue TO a new double-ended queue containing pairs of each node in the range from zero TO n MINUS one together with a value obtained by ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY node  
        SET visited TO a new set containing the same pairs as in queue  
      
        SET steps TO zero  
        SET all_nodes_visited TO ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY n MINUS one  
      
        WHILE queue is not empty  
            SET current_level_size TO the LENGTH OF queue  
            FOR iteration FROM one TO current_level_size  
                REMOVE the leftmost element from queue and DESCTRUCTURE INTO current_node and visited_nodes  
              
                IF visited_nodes EQUALS all_nodes_visited THEN  
                    RETURN steps  
                END IF  
              
                FOR each neighbor IN the element at position current_node of graph  
                    SET next_visited_nodes TO visited_nodes OR ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY neighbor  
                    SET next_state TO pair of neighbor and next_visited_nodes  
                  
                    IF next_state NOT IN visited THEN  
                        ADD next_state TO visited  
                        APPEND next_state TO queue  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END FOR  
          
            INCREMENT steps BY one  
        END WHILE  
      
        RETURN negative one  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

        END FUNCTION

        END FOR  
        
        RETURN answer

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION movesToStamp(stamp string, target string) RETURNS list of integers  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF stamp  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF target  
        SET indeg TO a list of size n MINUS m PLUS one where each element is m  
        SET q TO an empty double ended queue  
        SET g TO a list of size n where each element is an empty list  
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS m  
            FOR j FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
                SET c TO element at position j of stamp  
                IF element at position i PLUS j of target EQUALS c THEN  
                    DECREMENT element at position i of indeg BY one  
                    IF element at position i of indeg EQUALS zero THEN  
                        APPEND i TO q  
                    END IF  
                ELSE  
                    APPEND i TO element at position i PLUS j of g  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        SET ans TO an empty list  
        SET vis TO a list of size n where each element is False  
        WHILE q is not empty  
            SET i TO the element removed from the left of q  
            APPEND i TO ans  
            FOR j FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
                IF element at position i PLUS j of vis EQUALS False THEN  
                    SET element at position i PLUS j of vis TO True  
                    FOR each k IN element at position i PLUS j of g  
                        DECREMENT element at position k of indeg BY one  
                        IF element at position k of indeg EQUALS zero THEN  
                            APPEND k TO q  
                        END IF  
                    END FOR  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END WHILE  
        IF all elements of vis are True THEN  
            RETURN ans in reverse order  
        ELSE  
            RETURN an empty list  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION distinctSubseqII(s)  
        SET MOD TO ten POWER nine PLUS seven  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s  
        SET dp TO a list OF zeroes WITH LENGTH n PLUS one  
        SET the element at position zero of dp TO one  
        SET last TO an empty mapping  
        FOR i FROM one TO n  
            SET char TO the element at position i MINUS one of s  
            SET the element at position i of dp TO the element at position i MINUS one of dp MULTIPLIED BY two  
            SET the element at position i of dp TO the element at position i of dp MODULO MOD  
            IF char EXISTS IN the keys OF last  
                SET the element at position i of dp TO the element at position i of dp MINUS the element at position last at char MINUS one of dp PLUS MOD  
                SET the element at position i of dp TO the element at position i of dp MODULO MOD  
            END IF  
            ASSIGN last at char TO i  
        END FOR  
        RETURN the element at position n of dp MINUS one MODULO MOD  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION canConvert WITH PARAMETERS str1 str2  
        IF str1 EQUALS str2  
            RETURN True  
        END IF  
        SET conversion_map TO an empty mapping from characters to characters  
        FOR each pair of characters char1 and char2 FROM str1 AND str2 in order  
            IF char1 IS IN conversion_map  
                IF the value mapped from char1 in conversion_map NOT EQUALS char2  
                    RETURN False  
                END IF  
            ELSE  
                SET the value mapped from char1 in conversion_map TO char2  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        IF the number of unique characters IN str2 EQUALS twenty six  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION sortItems(n, m, group, beforeItems)  
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            IF element at position i of group EQUALS minus one  
                SET element at position i of group TO m  
                INCREMENT m BY one  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        
        SET group_items TO a mapping from keys to empty lists  
        SET group_graph TO a mapping from keys to empty lists  
        SET item_graph TO a mapping from keys to empty lists  
        SET item_in_degree TO a list consisting of zero repeated n times  
        SET group_in_degree TO a list consisting of zero repeated m times  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            APPEND i TO list at key element at position i of group in group_items  
        END FOR  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            FOR each before_element IN element at position i of beforeItems  
                IF element at position before_element of group EQUALS element at position i of group  
                    APPEND i TO list at key before_element in item_graph  
                    INCREMENT element at position i of item_in_degree BY one  
                ELSE  
                    APPEND element at position i of group TO list at key element at position before_element of group in group_graph  
                    INCREMENT element at position element at position i of group of group_in_degree BY one  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        FUNCTION topological_sort(graph, in_degree, items)  
            SET queue TO a double-ended queue initialized with elements from items WHERE element at position element of in_degree EQUALS zero  
            SET result TO empty list  
            
            WHILE queue is not empty  
                REMOVE element from front of queue and assign to u  
                APPEND u TO result  
                FOR each v IN list at key u in graph  
                    DECREMENT element at position v of in_degree BY one  
                    IF element at position v of in_degree EQUALS zero  
                        APPEND v TO queue  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END WHILE  
            
            IF LENGTH OF result EQUALS LENGTH OF items  
                RETURN result  
            ELSE  
                RETURN empty list  
            END IF  
        END FUNCTION  
        
        SET sorted_within_groups TO empty list  
        FOR each items_list IN all values of group_items  
            SET sorted_items TO topological_sort(item_graph, item_in_degree, items_list)  
            IF LENGTH OF sorted_items EQUALS zero  
                RETURN empty list  
            END IF  
            EXTEND sorted_within_groups BY sorted_items  
        END FOR  
        
        SET sorted_groups TO topological_sort(group_graph, group_in_degree, list of elements from zero TO m MINUS one)  
        IF LENGTH OF sorted_groups EQUALS zero  
            RETURN empty list  
        END IF  
        
        SET group_to_items_map TO a mapping from keys to empty lists  
        FOR each item IN sorted_within_groups  
            APPEND item TO list at key element at position item of group in group_to_items_map  
        END FOR  
        
        SET result TO empty list  
        FOR each grp IN sorted_groups  
            EXTEND result BY list at key grp in group_to_items_map  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN result  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION countVowelPermutation(n)  
        SET MOD TO ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten MULTIPLIED BY ten PLUS seven  
        SET a TO one  
        SET e TO one  
        SET i TO one  
        SET o TO one  
        SET u TO one  
        FOR each index FROM two TO n  
            SET a_next TO the sum of e PLUS i PLUS u  
            SET e_next TO the sum of a PLUS i  
            SET i_next TO the sum of e PLUS o  
            SET o_next TO i  
            SET u_next TO the sum of i PLUS o  
            SET a TO the remainder when a_next is DIVIDED BY MOD  
            SET e TO the remainder when e_next is DIVIDED BY MOD  
            SET i TO the remainder when i_next is DIVIDED BY MOD  
            SET o TO the remainder when o_next is DIVIDED BY MOD  
            SET u TO the remainder when u_next is DIVIDED BY MOD  
        END FOR  
        SET total_count TO the sum of a PLUS e PLUS i PLUS o PLUS u  
        SET result TO the remainder when total_count is DIVIDED BY MOD  
        RETURN result  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION numberOfArrays(s PARAMETER string, k PARAMETER integer) RETURNS integer  
        SET MOD TO one billion PLUS seven  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s  
        INITIALIZE dp AS a list of n PLUS one zeros  
        SET element at position zero of dp TO one  
        FOR i FROM one TO n  
            FOR j FROM zero TO i MINUS one  
                IF character at position j of s NOT EQUALS zero AND  
                   the integer value of substring from position j TO position i MINUS one of s GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO one AND  
                   the integer value of substring from position j TO position i MINUS one of s LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO k  
                THEN  
                    SET element at position i of dp TO the sum of element at position i of dp AND element at position j of dp MODULO MOD  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN element at position n of dp  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION kthSmallest(mat AS List OF List OF Integer k AS Integer) RETURNS Integer  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF mat  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF the element at position zero of mat  
        SET initial_sum TO zero  
        FOR each row IN mat  
            INCREMENT initial_sum BY the element at position zero of row  
        END FOR  
        SET initial_indices TO a tuple of zero repeated m times  
        SET min_heap TO a list containing a tuple of initial_sum and initial_indices  
        SET visited TO a set containing initial_indices  
        
        WHILE k GREATER THAN zero  
            EXTRACT the tuple containing current_sum and indices by removing the smallest element from min_heap  
            DECREMENT k BY one  
            
            IF k EQUALS zero  
                RETURN current_sum  
            END IF  
            
            FOR i FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
                IF the element at position i of indices PLUS one LESS THAN n  
                    SET new_indices_list TO a list converted from indices  
                    INCREMENT the element at position i of new_indices_list BY one  
                    SET new_indices_tuple TO a tuple converted from new_indices_list  
                    SET new_sum TO current_sum MINUS the element at position i of mat AT the element at position i of indices PLUS the element at position i of mat AT the element at position i of new_indices_tuple  
                    
                    IF new_indices_tuple NOT IN visited  
                        ADD new_indices_tuple TO visited  
                        ADD the tuple containing new_sum and new_indices_tuple TO min_heap  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END WHILE  
        
        RETURN negative one  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maxDotProduct(nums1 PARAMETER, nums2 PARAMETER)  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF nums1  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF nums2  
        SET dp TO a new list of lists where each inner list has n PLUS one elements each set TO negative infinity and the outer list has m PLUS one such inner lists  
        FOR i FROM one TO m  
            FOR j FROM one TO n  
                SET current_product TO the element at position i MINUS one of nums1 MULTIPLIED BY the element at position j MINUS one of nums2  
                SET dp element at position i element at position j TO the maximum of the following four values  
                    current_product  
                    dp element at position i MINUS one element at position j  
                    dp element at position i element at position j MINUS one  
                    dp element at position i MINUS one element at position j MINUS one PLUS current_product  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN dp element at position m element at position n  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION minimumEffort(tasks)  
        SORT tasks IN ORDER WHERE the element representing the difference between the second element MINUS the first element of each task IS IN DESCENDING ORDER  
        SET current_energy TO zero  
        SET required_initial_energy TO zero  
        FOR each element IN tasks  
            ASSIGN actual TO the first element of element  
            ASSIGN minimum TO the second element of element  
            IF current_energy LESS THAN minimum THEN  
                INCREMENT required_initial_energy BY minimum MINUS current_energy  
                SET current_energy TO minimum  
            END IF  
            DECREMENT current_energy BY actual  
        END FOR  
        RETURN required_initial_energy  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS UnionFind  
    FUNCTION __init__(self, size)  
        SET self.parent TO list of integers from zero TO size MINUS one  
        SET self.rank TO list containing size copies of one  
    END FUNCTION  

    FUNCTION find(self, p)  
        IF element at position p of self.parent NOT EQUALS p  
            SET element at position p of self.parent TO self.find(element at position p of self.parent)  
        END IF  
        RETURN element at position p of self.parent  
    END FUNCTION  

    FUNCTION union(self, p, q)  
        SET rootP TO self.find(p)  
        SET rootQ TO self.find(q)  
        IF rootP EQUALS rootQ  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        IF element at position rootP of self.rank GREATER THAN element at position rootQ of self.rank  
            SET element at position rootQ of self.parent TO rootP  
        ELSE IF element at position rootP of self.rank LESS THAN element at position rootQ of self.rank  
            SET element at position rootP of self.parent TO rootQ  
        ELSE  
            SET element at position rootQ of self.parent TO rootP  
            INCREMENT element at position rootP of self.rank BY one  
        END IF  
        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS  

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION gcdSort(self, nums)  
        SET sorted_nums TO nums sorted in ascending order  
        SET max_val TO the maximum value in nums  
        SET uf TO a new UnionFind object initialized with max_val PLUS one  

        FOR each num IN nums  
            FOR each factor FROM two TO the integer part of the square root of num PLUS one  
                IF num MODULO factor EQUALS zero  
                    CALL uf.union(num, factor)  
                    CALL uf.union(num, num DIVIDED BY factor)  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  

        FOR each i FROM zero TO the length of nums MINUS one  
            IF uf.find(element at position i of nums) NOT EQUALS uf.find(element at position i of sorted_nums)  
                RETURN False  
            END IF  
        END FOR  

        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumGood(statements)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF statements  
        SET max_good TO zero  
        FOR i FROM zero TO the NUMBER ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY n MINUS one  
            SET good TO a LIST OF n ELEMENTS EACH SET TO FALSE  
            SET bad TO a LIST OF n ELEMENTS EACH SET TO FALSE  
            FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
                IF the BITWISE AND of i AND the NUMBER ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY j EQUALS the NUMBER ONE SHIFTED LEFT BY j  
                    SET the element at position j of good TO TRUE  
                ELSE  
                    SET the element at position j of bad TO TRUE  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
            SET valid TO TRUE  
            FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one WHILE valid HOLDS  
                IF the element at position j of good EQUALS TRUE  
                    FOR k FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
                        IF the element at position j of statements AT position k EQUALS zero AND the element at position k of good EQUALS TRUE OR the element at position j of statements AT position k EQUALS one AND the element at position k of bad EQUALS TRUE  
                            SET valid TO FALSE  
                            BREAK the inner FOR loop  
                        END IF  
                    END FOR  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
            IF valid EQUALS TRUE  
                SET max_good TO the GREATER OF max_good AND the SUM OF elements in good WHERE each TRUE IS COUNTED AS one AND each FALSE AS zero  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN max_good  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumMinutes(grid)  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF grid  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF element at position zero of grid  
        SET directions TO the LIST of elements each being a PAIR consisting of one and zero MINUS one and zero zero and one zero and MINUS one  
        
        FUNCTION can_escape(wait)  
            SET fire_times TO a two-dimensional list of size m by n each element set TO infinity  
            SET queue TO an empty double-ended queue  
            
            FOR i FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
                FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
                    IF element at position i of grid EQUALS one  
                        APPEND the TRIPLE consisting of i j and zero TO queue  
                        SET element at position i and j of fire_times TO zero  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END FOR  
            
            WHILE queue is not empty  
                REMOVE the first element and ASSIGN its components TO x y and t  
                FOR each dx dy IN directions  
                    SET nx TO x PLUS dx  
                    SET ny TO y PLUS dy  
                    IF nx GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND nx LESS THAN m AND ny GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND ny LESS THAN n AND element at position nx and ny of grid EQUALS zero AND element at position nx and ny of fire_times EQUALS infinity  
                        SET element at position nx and ny of fire_times TO t PLUS one  
                        APPEND the TRIPLE consisting of nx ny and t PLUS one TO queue  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END WHILE  
            
            SET queue TO a double-ended queue containing a single TRIPLE consisting of zero zero and wait  
            SET visited TO a set containing the PAIR zero zero  
            
            WHILE queue is not empty  
                REMOVE the first element and ASSIGN its components TO x y and t  
                FOR each dx dy IN directions  
                    SET nx TO x PLUS dx  
                    SET ny TO y PLUS dy  
                    IF nx GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND nx LESS THAN m AND ny GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND ny LESS THAN n AND the PAIR nx ny NOT IN visited AND element at position nx and ny of grid EQUALS zero  
                        IF nx EQUALS m MINUS one AND ny EQUALS n MINUS one  
                            IF element at position nx and ny of fire_times GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO t PLUS one  
                                RETURN true  
                            ELSE  
                                RETURN false  
                            END IF  
                        END IF  
                        IF element at position nx and ny of fire_times GREATER THAN t PLUS one  
                            ADD the PAIR nx ny TO visited  
                            APPEND the TRIPLE consisting of nx ny and t PLUS one TO queue  
                        END IF  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END WHILE  
            
            RETURN false  
        END FUNCTION  
        
        SET left TO zero  
        SET right TO m MULTIPLIED BY n  
        SET result TO MINUS one  
        
        WHILE left LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO right  
            SET mid TO left PLUS right DIVIDED BY two rounded down to the nearest integer  
            IF can_escape(mid)  
                SET result TO mid  
                SET left TO mid PLUS one  
            ELSE  
                SET right TO mid MINUS one  
            END IF  
        END WHILE  
        
        IF result NOT EQUALS m MULTIPLIED BY n  
            RETURN result  
        ELSE  
            RETURN one followed by nine zeros  
        END IF  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION pacificAtlantic WITH PARAMETER heights  
        FUNCTION bfs WITH PARAMETERS q AND vis  
            WHILE the LENGTH OF q is greater than zero  
                FOR each element from zero TO the LENGTH OF q MINUS one  
                    SET i TO the first element of the element at position zero of q removed from the front  
                    SET j TO the second element of the element at position zero of q removed from the front  
                    FOR each pair a and b IN the list of pairs where the pairs are zero and MINUS one, zero and one, one and zero, MINUS one and zero  
                        SET x TO i PLUS a  
                        SET y TO j PLUS b  
                        IF x GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND x LESS THAN m AND y GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero AND y LESS THAN n AND the tuple consisting of x and y is NOT IN vis AND the element at position x of heights AT position y OF heights GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO the element at position i of heights AT position j OF heights  
                            ADD the tuple consisting of x and y TO vis  
                            APPEND the tuple consisting of x and y TO the end of q  
                        END IF  
                    END FOR  
                END FOR  
            END WHILE  
        END FUNCTION  

        SET m TO the LENGTH OF heights  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF the element at position zero of heights  
        SET vis1 TO an empty set  
        SET vis2 TO an empty set  
        SET q1 TO an empty double ended queue  
        SET q2 TO an empty double ended queue  
        FOR i FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
            FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
                IF i EQUALS zero OR j EQUALS zero  
                    ADD the tuple consisting of i and j TO vis1  
                    APPEND the tuple consisting of i and j TO the end of q1  
                END IF  
                IF i EQUALS m MINUS one OR j EQUALS n MINUS one  
                    ADD the tuple consisting of i and j TO vis2  
                    APPEND the tuple consisting of i and j TO the end of q2  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        CALL bfs WITH q1 AND vis1  
        CALL bfs WITH q2 AND vis2  
        SET result TO an empty list  
        FOR i FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
            FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
                IF the tuple consisting of i and j IS IN vis1 AND the tuple consisting of i and j IS IN vis2  
                    APPEND the tuple consisting of i and j TO result  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN result  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS
